# No Backwards Compatibility

This project does not require backwards compatibility. Prefer clean, direct changes over compatibility shims.

## Guidelines

- **Rename freely**: Update call sites instead of keeping old aliases.
- **Delete deprecated code**: Remove unused functions, fields, and code paths instead of marking them deprecated.
- **Break APIs when warranted**: Change function signatures, payload shapes, config keys, and storage formats without keeping legacy fallbacks.
- **No migration shims**: Don't add adapters, version flags, or "if old format" branches just to support prior behavior.
- **No deprecation warnings**: Just remove the thing.

## Examples

```js
// BAD: keeping a legacy alias "for backwards compatibility"
export function loadMap(name) { /* new impl */ }
export const load_map = loadMap; // legacy

// GOOD: rename and update callers
export function loadMap(name) { /* new impl */ }
```

```js
// BAD: dual-path to support old payload shape
function handle(msg) {
  if (msg.v === 1) return handleV1(msg);
  return handleV2(msg);
}

// GOOD: migrate the format and delete v1
function handle(msg) {
  return handleV2(msg);
}
```

## No Exceptions

There are no carve-outs. There is no save functionality, and SGNL schemas/contracts are owned by this repo and managed by the dedicated SGNL skill — not by backwards-compatibility shims here.
